FizzBuzz
16
...
$
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>15 is replaced by FizzBuzz, because itâ€™s evenly divisible by 3 and 5, and the rest of the numbers print out normally.</p>

<h2 id="print-fizz-if-the-number-is-a-multiple-of-three-and-buzz-if-its-a-multiple-of-five">Print â€œFizzâ€ if the Number Is a Multiple of Three and â€œBuzzâ€ if Itâ€™s a Multiple of Five</h2>

<p>To handle the other two cases of the Fizz-Buzz problem, weâ€™ll need to utilize <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">elif</code> statements for each of the individual comparisons that we used in our <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">if</code> statement. Letâ€™s add those now:</p>

<p><strong>~/fizz-buzz.py</strong></p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>#!/usr/bin/env python3.7

upper_number = int(input("How many values should we process: "))

for number in range(1, upper_number + 1):
  if number % 3 == 0 and number % 5 == 0:
      print("FizzBuzz")
  elif value % 3 == 0:
      print("Fizz")
